The UN-sponsored climate conference -- hitherto characterized by disorganized assignments and mutual recriminations -- came back under the spotlight on Friday, with a document outlining ambitious greenhouse gas reductions over the next 40 years, with industrialized nations supporting most of them in the coming years.
