The United States will not sign an agreement without efforts and actions from major developing countries, Stern said, also regretting that the text does not insist enough to ensure that the cuts could be verified by outside observers.
Stern made his comments an hour after China's Deputy Foreign Minister He Yafei said the U.S. chief negotiator either lacked "common sense" or was "extremely irresponsible" for saying earlier this week that the United States would not help China financially to fight global warming.
With the future economic trajectories of the major world powers at stake, flaws have emerged both within the Third World and between the industrial world and emerging economies.
