Distribution (distribution)
This apparent paradox is explained by the complex money-sharing procedure applied by UEFA.
For this year, the organization chaired by Michel Platini expects to earn 1,090 million thanks to the Champions League.
Of this sum, UEFA will allocate <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>413.1 million to fixed payments: each of the 20 clubs that participated in the qualifying matches (among which Atlético de Madrid) received <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>2.1 million.
